## Plan Summary

After thoroughly exploring the codebase, here is the complete implementation plan for adding the `mistral-instruct-v3` handler to `common/chat.cpp`.

---

### Key findings from exploration

- `autoparser::generation_params::messages` is of type `json` (`nlohmann::ordered_json`) — iterable with `msg.value("role", "")` / `msg.value("content", "")`
- The existing **Ministral/Mistral Large 3** handler (line 1638–1644) already checks for `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — the new handler must **exclude** templates with `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to avoid collision
- `tmpl.bos_token()` provides the `<s>` BOS token for the prompt prefix
- `COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` is the correct enum value (no PEG parser needed for this simple format)

---

### Change 1: New handler function (insert after line 1517, before `common_chat_try_specialized_template`)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_content;
    bool        first_user = true;
    bool        bos_added  = false;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_content = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (!bos_added) {
                data.prompt += tmpl.bos_token();
                bos_added = true;
            }
            data.prompt += "[INST] ";
            if (first_user && !system_content.empty()) {
                data.prompt += system_content + "\n";
                first_user = false;
            }
            data.prompt += content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

